<HL>
   Who's News:
   Black &amp; Decker Picks
   Hammes of Chrysler
   To Lead Largest Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
05/16/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7
</SO>
<CO>
   BDK WNEWS C
</CO>
<LP>
   TOWSON, Md. -- Black &amp; Decker Corp., as expected, named
Michael N. Hammes, Chrysler Corp.'s vice president of
international operations, to the post of executive vice
president.
   Mr. Hammes, 48 years old, will head Black &amp; Decker's
largest unit, the $2 billion Power Tools and Home Improvement
Group. Mr. Hammes, who joined Chrysler in 1986 after almost
30 years with Ford Motor Co., has extensive experience in
international operations and joint-venture activities.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Black &amp; Decker has been searching for an executive with
global experience to fill the job since February when George
M. Sherman left the company to become president of Danaher
Corp.
</TEXT>
